#MEM id=examples source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/executive-operations/roadmap-planning/examples/sample.md
M|examples|**ctx:** Annual planning, need to align roadmap with retention and enterprise expansion goals.
M|examples|**Phase 1 - Gather Inputs:**
M|examples|- Business goals: Reduce churn from 15% to 8%, increase enterprise deals from 2/quarter to 5/quarter
M|examples|- Customer problems: Onboarding confusion, enterprise SSO gap, mobile access issues
M|examples|- tec: Need to upgrade data pl for advanced reporting
M|examples|**Phase 2 - Define Epics:**
M|examples|- Wrote 12 epics with hypotheses (guided onboarding, enterprise SSO, mobile workflows, advanced reporting, etc.)
M|examples|- Estimated effort: Onboarding = M (3 weeks), SSO = M (4 weeks), Mobile = L (2 months)
M|examples|**Phase 3 - Prioritize:**
M|examples|- Used RICE framework (recommended by `prioritization-advisor.md`)
M|examples|- Scored: Onboarding (24,000), SSO (675), Mobile (2,000), Reporting (1,000)
M|examples|- Strategic override: Boosted SSO priority (critical for enterprise expansion)
M|examples|**Phase 4 - Sequence:**
M|examples|- Q1: Guided Onboarding, Enterprise SSO, Mobile Workflows
M|examples|- Q2: Advanced Reporting (depends on Data pl in Q1), Slack Integration
M|examples|- Q3: Mobile App (depends on API Redesign)
M|examples|**Phase 5 - Communicate:**
M|examples|- Presented to execs: "Q1 focuses on retention (onboarding) and enterprise expansion (SSO)"
M|examples|- Feedback: "Can we add pricing page redesign to Q2?" → Adjusted roadmap
M|examples|- Published: Internal roadmap (Confluence), external roadmap (Now/Next/Later)
M|examples|**Outcome:** Clear, aligned roadmap with strategic narrative.
M|examples|**ctx:** PM creates roadmap alone, based on stakeholder requests.
M|examples|**Phase 1 - Gather Inputs:** Skipped (no business goals rv)
M|examples|**Phase 2 - Define Epics:** Listed features requested by sales, mkt, CS
M|examples|**Phase 3 - Prioritize:** Prioritized by "who shouted loudest"
M|examples|**Phase 4 - Sequence:** Threw features into Q1, Q2, Q3 with no rationale
M|examples|**Phase 5 - Communicate:** Presented feature list to execs
M|examples|**Why this failed:**
M|examples|- No strategic narrative ("Why are we building this?")
M|examples|- No customer problems framed
M|examples|- No hypotheses or success metrics
M|examples|- Roadmap felt like random feature list
M|examples|**Fix with roadmap planning workflow:**
M|examples|- **Phase 1:** rv business goals (reduce churn, increase enterprise)
M|examples|- **Phase 2:** Turn feature requests into epics with hypotheses
M|examples|- **Phase 3:** Prioritize by RICE (impact + effort), not politics
M|examples|- **Phase 4:** Sequence logically by dependencies, business goals
M|examples|- **Phase 5:** Present with narrative: "Q1 = Retention, Q2 = Enterprise Expansion"